New Records: Victor Wembanyama became just the third player in NBA history to record multiple 5x5 games, joining Hakeem Olajuwon and Andrei Kirilenko.
Key Match Events: Victor Wembanyama logged 25 points, nine rebounds, seven assists, five steals, and five blocks.
Chris Paul put up 19 points, seven rebounds, and 10 assists, shooting 8-of-13 from the field.
Sandro Mamukelashvili scored 10 points off the bench in just 10 minutes of play.
